tags: but I flipping love figure skating
summary: @idkanatomy‘s awesome artwork lit a fire under my ass so now y’all gonna have to deal with my Marvel figure skating meta head...
body:
@idkanatomy‘s awesome artwork lit a fire under my ass so now y’all gonna have to deal with my Marvel figure skating meta head canons before I go run off to read that fic:

Tony’s style would be very Javi, a lot of emphasis on step sequences and story telling. He’d have high PCS and could land a quad lutz in the first half of his routine, but step sequences and triple axels are his bread and butter. Last of the older style of skating (re: PCS > TES), wears his emotions on his sleeve, elegant landings and the funniest exhibition skates you’ve ever seen. Instagram famous. Instagram Lives his practice routines and you’re pretty much a nobody until you’ve gotten a selfie with Tony on his page.

Steve’s a total quad king. His routines are built around those quads, and particularly staggered towards the end of his skates for the double points, incredibly high TES. Not the best at expressing emotions and feelings in his skates and depending on how his practice goes, he tends to flub jumps. Thanks to the overwhelming amount of quads in his repertoire, he always lands somewhere on the podium even if many in the figure skating community find his skating stiff and repetitive. Socially anxious, tends to avoid interviews, but is pressured into joining instagram by Tony. Mostly shares photos of sunrises on his morning runs, photos of his lunch and a million snaps of his dog.

Natasha and James are a major threat in the pairs world. Perennial podium placement. Eerily efficient and sequenced skates. I honestly could see them as either figure skating pairs or ice dancers. They’d nail the choreography. Haters call them the Russian robots and are convinced they can read each others minds. Completely avoids the media, no one knows if they’re friends or something more. Natasha was caught photobombing one of Tony’s IG live practices before the GPF.

Peter:...
body:
Stephen: Looks like I got here just in time
Tony: What do you mean, just in time?
Stephen: You were in a lot of trouble
Peter: Trouble? We were just searching for the last HYDRA agents
Tony: *coughing* Yeah, we had the situation well under control, Dumbledore
Stephen: Mhm, I see. So which part of the situation did you have under control: the blocked entrance, the poison gas, or that tank right behind you?
